posts.description:
MAP UPDATE
— 78% — 
Slowly getting closer and closer to the finish line. Hoping to complete all 196 countries by 2018. For now Congo will be my last stop in Africa. It's time for some rest and relaxation! 🚢☀️🌴🍹Thank you as always to everyone following along! 🙏🏼❤️ خیلی ممنون
Diosso Gorge — known as the "Grand Canyon of Congo🇨🇬"

I get lots of messages everyday from you guys telling me how I've become your inspiration. I always feel so grateful when I read those wonderful messages. Thank you!! 🙏🏼❤️ So I decided I would share with you MY inspiration. The people in my life that inspire, and motivate me to keep going. Without them, I simply wouldn't be where I am today!
➖
(This family photo was taken at my brother Joel's wedding a few years ago.)
➖
Mom — My number one fan! Always waiting on my next post to make sure I'm still alive! 😁 Without your prayers I'm sure I would've already been captured by Somali pirates or worse. Thank you Mom for always believing in me. Te amo! ❤️
➖
Ethan — Little bro, I think I remember you once saying something like... "What's good in having a popular brother on IG if I never get tagged?" ............. 👉🏼 @ethanswims 👈🏼...... Ladies, he's on the swim team 🏊 at King University. Please flood his account with many many follow requests. 😁
➖
Joel — I've been waiting on a niece or nephew for quite a while now! Could you and Kayla get to work already?!😁
➖
Angie — My little Filipina sister. 🇵🇭 I know things haven't always been the easiest, but you've come such a long way, and I'm really proud of you! (Huwag kailanman kalimutan kung saan ka nagsimula!)
➖
JC — Congratulations on your recent engagement bro! So happy for you! 🎉 I just can't believe that I haven't even met her yet. 😕 I've really been away from home for way too damn long! You can be sure I'll be at that wedding!
➖
Dad — I got my travel genes from you. You've traveled extensively all over the world, and have even been to some places that I haven't! 😱 You also taught me everything I know about photography. So when people compliment my pictures, they're actually complementing you. I will forever be grateful for showing me the way! 🙏🏼
➖
I miss you all so much ❤️, and hope to be back home soon. I really need a break from Africa!!!

Shipwreck Beach — just north of Luanda. Such an interesting place to see!!! I didn't count them all, but my guess is at least 20 of these old rusted ships are littered along the beach shore. (Maybe even more!)

It's such a shame they only gave me a 5 day visa for Angola. Which unfortunately means I only have 1 day left in this beautiful country. I really dislike going to places just for the sake of getting a stamp on my passport. I mean really what the hell is the point of doing that!? When I go somewhere new I like to explore, see the country, and spend time meeting with locals. Otherwise you end up visiting all 196 countries, and seeing absolutely nothing! (There's a girl on IG that just did exactly that.) Anyhow, I'm most certainly coming back to Angola, and next time with at least a 30 day visa.
Miradouro de Lua — (40 kilometers south of Luanda) An incredibly beautiful natural landscape shaped over time by wind and rain erosion.

I'm gonna miss this paradise!! ❤️São Tomé is an incredibly beautiful country with some truly out of this world scenery! 😍 Friendly people, awesome food, and all around very affordable. Highly recommended!! ⭐️ ⭐️ ⭐️ ⭐️ ⭐️ ❤️ 🇸🇹

Last full day on the beautiful island of São Tomé. I don't wanna leave!! 😭😭 I'm flying out tomorrow night to country 152. If you're following along on Telegram then you probably already know where I'm going! (But if not, then we'll just let it be a surprise!) 😁
If you don't hear from me for about a month or two... This is where I'll be - sipping on caipirinhas. 🍹🌴☀️ #NeverLeaving 🇸🇹❤️
Beautiful Praia Jalé 😍 on the southern tip of São Tomé. Pretty much had the entire beach to myself. It's absolute paradise here!!! 🌴☀️❤️ Who wants to join!?? 😁
